  "body": "## Simple Summary\r\nSupport a mode compiling Vyper contracts for the OVM\r\n\r\n## Motivation\r\nThe Optimistic Virtual Machine (OVM) is designed to support Layer 2 smart contract interactions in the Optimisitic Rollup Layer 2 framework. It is likely to be very popular given initial support for Uniswap and other major contract systems, so we should support it.\r\n\r\n## Specification\r\nFrom a user standpoint, this would be enabling a flag to target the OVM instead of the EVM as a target. The actual mechanics of how this works is fairly simple, basically you need to swap out all \"system calls\" such as environment variables and SSTORE/SLOAD to use their OVM equivalents. The PR for patching Solidity with support is here: https://github.com/ethereum-optimism/solidity/pull/1\r\n\r\n## Backwards Compatibility\r\nNo backwards compatibility issues\r\n\r\n## Dependencies\r\nNo dependencies\r\n\r\n## References\r\nhttps://medium.com/@optimismPBC/light-at-the-end-of-the-tunnel-c390a05bbcb8\r\nhttps://github.com/ethereum-optimism/contracts-v2/blob/ad5e11860a2b1b25e886e5fdec46b1afb7a5372d/contracts/optimistic-ethereum/iOVM/execution/iOVM_ExecutionManager.sol#L85\r\n\r\n## Copyright\r\nCopyright and related rights waived via [CC0](https://creativecommons.org/publicdomain/zero/1.0/)\r\n",
